# Git commit identity (Momentum / Osys)

When creating commits in **this repository**, always use the shared team identity:

- **Name:** `Osys Office`
- **Email:** `osys.office.abc@gmail.com`

## Before committing

1. Verify repo-local config (do not use global `git config` unless the user explicitly asks):
   ```bash
   git config user.email   # must be osys.office.abc@gmail.com
   git config user.name    # must be Osys Office
   ```
2. If missing, set **local** config only:
   ```bash
   git config --local user.email "osys.office.abc@gmail.com"
   git config --local user.name "Osys Office"
   ```
3. Never commit with personal emails (e.g. `mitakashimezukirin@gmail.com`) in this project.

## Notes

- Push auth may still use the developer's GitHub login; only **commit author** metadata should show Osys Office.
- Do not amend or rewrite history to change author unless the user explicitly requests it.
